embeds.title: New Charter Policy Announcement:
embeds.description:
Dear fellow members, 

The Chief Officers have voted to implement a new Charter Policy for our Virtual Airline. We believe our VA has if not the most, one of the most unique ways of doing charter operations of any VA out there. We Believe our members should be able to fly anywhere at anytime. This new policy only effects flights that are not on our flight schedule. "Bookable" routes that are on the schedule remain the same. 

We believe this policy will greatly benefit FedEx Virtual in a multitude of ways.
~Allows members to have items to use role income credits and casino credits on.
~Allows more engagement tools for staff.
~Rewards the hard work of our Logistics Team.

This policy will go into effect officially on January 31st, 2021. So pilots may continue flying non "bookable" routes as normal at no cost, until **January 31st, 2021.** Pilots that choose to, may go ahead and begin using the new Charters Channel located under the Lounge category. Once this policy goes into effect, PIREPS filled with a flight number of FDX-CTR will require a charter item purchase and usage in order for that PIREP to be accepted.

In an attempt to clear up some confusion when it comes to filing PIREPS, please familiarize yourself with these diagrams. They will hopefully make the process easier when filing PIREPs after completing your flight, as well as expedite the process of getting your flight hours logged. We’ve included a sample dispatch sheet and PIREP for you to reference. The areas containing information on the dispatch sheet have a number assigned that matches the area on the PIREP sheet where the information should be entered. For example, the data on the dispatch sheet with a #1 next to it should be entered in the box on the PIREP sheet that has a #1 next to it. *Remember, at no time do you need to manually enter the callsign, call number, etc that you selected upon joining FDXV.* The only flight number or identifying information you need to enter is on the dispatch sheet next to the red #1. Hopefully this guide will help make your experience with FDXV even more enjoyable. As always, if you do have any questions or need further assistance please do not hesitate to ask any of the @deleted-role .

*Also, for any flights that are part of a special program or sanctioned event, you will use the specialized flight number associated with that type of program or event. So, for a #deleted-channel flight, the flight number will be FDX TRADE. If you use a charter, the flight number is FDX CTR. If you participate in an event, it will normally be FDX EVENT. If the flight number needs to be something different, there will be an announcement or notification.*

*Remember, only list the actual flight hours flown. The specialized flight number associated with routes that award bonus flight hours will be recognized by the @deleted-role and they will credit you with the bonus hours when your PIREP is processed.*

@everyone,

**Discord Voice Chat Streaming**

*As per the IFVARB policy change on this, we at FDXV will allow streaming within a voice channel. We have elected to adopt the IFVARB policy as is with the exception that only Infinite Flight related material be screen shared. Examples of this would include:* 

**➲┃Infinite Flight user flights**
**➲┃IF Twitch streams**
**➲┃IF YouTube videos**

As per the IFVARB policy a staff member **Must** be present in order to stream. 

**IFVARB Policy:**

Voice communications are a privilege that can be restricted from any VA/VO at the discretion of the IFVARB and or IFC Moderation team. (January 2021)

The CEO/Person Responsible of a VA/VO is ultimately responsible for moderating voice channels and its contents. The IFVARB will NOT moderate voice communications and any issues within voice channels will be handled by the VA/VO. 

VA/VOs are responsible for maintaining communications up to IFC standards, IFC rules surrounding acceptable communications should be the VA/VO's guide towards acceptable content. We leave access permissions of voice channels up to the VA/VO staff on who may partake in them. All voice channels must be regulated by a VA/VO in order to ensure that user safety is maintained at all times. Unregulated voice channels are prohibited.

Voice recording in any channel is strictly prohibited. Staff meetings and VA/VO meetings can be recorded with explicit written permission of all parties involved.

Voice ATC operations are STRICTLY prohibited within all VA/VO communities.

Streaming within Discord voice channels (VCs) is ALLOWED only when a staff member is present to moderate channel activity. Webcam video sharing remains PROHIBITED.

Infinite Flight and the IFVARB are independent of any voice communications that take place within the VA/VO community. VA/VOs that are in breach of these regulations will have its voice communication hosting privileges revoked.

Dear @Crew Member, due to a recent change in the IFVARB activity check-in procedures we will be changing a few things related to our special program pirep's and bonuses. Effective today and going forward all members will need to include any applicable bonuses in their pireps at the time of filing. **Now all event, trade network, ROTW, and AOTW** flights must file the bonuses at the time of filing. ━━━━━━━━━━━━
@IFATC Member's - 
Please use the regular pirep form to submit your ATC pireps. you may submit a support ticket if you need help.  An example will be below:

Flight number will be: **FX ATC**
Departure & Arrival: KMEM - KMEM
Flight time: is the amount of time you controlled.
all other fields you may place a "1" in. 
━━━━━━━━━━━━
**PIREP Form Update:**

Due to the increased duration times of flights because of the added bonusses, the pirep form has been updated to allow for up to a maximum of 40 hours & 59 minutes. **All pilots are strongly encouraged to utilize the comments section by indicating if a bonus was added and what type to reduce the risk of receiving a pirep rejection.**
━━━━━━━━━━━━
**Multiplier Calculator**

A multiplier calculator has been provided at the bottom of the form to help calculate your flight durations. An example would be :

**3:46 flight x1.5 (Chairman Club Bonus) = 5:39 Flight duration.** You would file a total duration of 5:39
━━━━━━━━━━━━

Over the last month the FedEx Virtual Chairmen Team have been working to reduce operational complexity on the back end of the VA. Over the last year, our staff have been doing weekly promotions which required 2-3 hours of reviewing each and every member from our CC roster and Discord roster.

*2. This will allow FDXV pilots to receive their Discord promotions sooner vs waiting until the end of the week.*

**A new custom command as been created to aid members when requesting for their Discord Promotions. "?promotions"**.

**__FAQ__**

*Q. How do I know when I should request a promotion?*

*A. Check your Crew Center profile - Does your cc rank match your Discord rank?*

**If not, request a promotion!**


*Those that do not request their promotions, will automatically rank up on the CC, however without notification their Discord Server ranks will remain the same.*

*Due to the recent changes that have came with the latest VAbase update we are forced to make changes to the way we operate with bonuses. As of now we are unable to accommodate pireps that exceed 23 hours and 59 minutes. Please understand that this not something we can control or edit.*

**__PIREPs:__ -**

- The maximum amount of hours one can now file a pirep for is now 23 hours and 59 minutes. Anything over that you will not get credit for it nor will you receive an adjustment for it.

- Every field on the PIREP form must have something entered into it so that the PIREP will be submitted.

- The #╭flight-logs channel will no longer be used by the pirep staff to communicate pirep approval / rejection. Members that file a pirep and wish to check the status my do so on the crew center by visiting the "Logbook & History" page. There you will find all pireps you have submitted and may check the status by clicking on any flight listed.

- PIREPs that are rejected will be communicated automatically by the crew center to the members by sending a email to the email address you have on file. Please visit the crew center and visit the edit profile tab to review your on file email address.  

**__BONUSES:__ -**

*Effective today we will not allow bonus stacking due to crew center limitations. The following is how bonuses are to be used:*

- Club Bonus will remain at 1.5X and not be combinable with any other bonus type. 

- Rank Bonuses will only be allowed on schedule / unofficial group flights / charter flights. 

- ROTW/ Priority bonus will remain at 1.5X and not be combinable with any other bonus type. 

- Event Bonuses will remain at 2X and not be combinable with any other bonus type. 

**__CHARTERS:__ -**

- Members that are of the rank of @First Officer and higher that wish to operate a charter route may continue to do so with any applicable rank bonus they have earned. Please note and understand that the **max  fileable ** flight time is 23 hours and 59 minutes including bonus. Anything over 23:59 you will not get credit for it.

:megaphone: **Reporting Fuel on PIREPs** :megaphone: 

Greetings @Crew Member's

I just wanted to reach out to everyone to make a quick announcement regarding reporting fuel on a PIREP. Every member should be reporting the fuel that is listed in the IF app and not from any third party site as it varies tremendously. This has caused a number of PIREPs to be denied because the fuel is not accurate at all. We want to avoid this completely.

I have attached a cheat sheet below which was created by our @PIREP Director which is the average fuel burn per hour for each of the FedEx aircraft in our fleet. Please keep in mind this fuel burn was taken directly from the IF app. Please use this cheat sheet and/or your reported Fuel Usage from the IF app when reporting your fuel on PIREPs to avoid possible denial.

We are 100% aware that fuel can vary depending on speed, altitude, etc. We just want to use this as a general guideline to avoid PIREPs being denied due to completely inaccurate fuel usage. 

Fuel Burn/Hour: 
MD-11F - 18,589 lbs
B77F - 14,731 lbs
DC-10F - 12,535 lbs
767 - 9,427 lbs
757 - 7,516 lbs
737 - 5,564 lbs
C208 - 362 lbs

If any member has any question regarding this please feel free to open up a support ticket in the #╰support-channel and a member of our @Director's will be more than happy to help.

Respectfully,
